duce the valid garden [1,1,1] to have a total beauty of 1 + 1 + 1 = 3.\\r\n\\r\n\\r\nExample 3:\\r\n\\r\n\\r\nInput: flowers = [-1,-2,0,-1]\\r\nOutput: -2\\r\nExplanation: You can produce the valid garden [-1,-1] to have a total beauty of -1 + -1 = -2.\\r\n\\r\n\\r\n \\r\nConstraints:\\r\n\\r\n\\r\n\t2 <= flowers.length <= 105\\r\n\t-104 <= flowers[i] <= 104\\r\n\tIt is possible to create a valid garden by removing some (possibly none) flowers.\\r\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def maximumBeauty(self, flowers: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def maximumBeauty(self, flowers: List[int]) -> int:\n        # Dictionary to store the first and last occurrence of each beauty value\n        first_occurrence = {}\n        last_occurrence = {}\n        prefix_sum = [0] * (len(flowers) + 1)\n        \n        # Calculate prefix sums and track first and last occurrences\n        for i, beauty in enumerate(flowers):\n            if beauty not in first_occurrence:\n                first_occurrence[beauty] = i\n            last_occurrence[beauty] = i\n            prefix_sum[i + 1] = prefix_sum[i] + max(0, beauty)  # only add positive beauties to prefix sum\n        \n        max_beauty = float('-inf')\n        \n        # Calculate the maximum beauty of valid gardens\n        for beauty in first_occurrence:\n            start = first_occurrence[beauty]\n            end = last_occurrence[beauty]\n            if start != end:\n                total_beauty = 2 * beauty + (prefix_sum[end] - prefix_sum[start + 1])\n                max_beauty = max(max_beauty, total_beauty)\n        \n        return max_beauty\n```\n\nThis solution works as follows:\n\n1. **Initialization**: We use two dictionaries to store the first and last occurrence of each beauty value in the `flowers` list. We also initialize a `prefix_sum` list to store the cumulative sum of positive beauty values.\n\n2. **Prefix Sum Calculation**: As we iterate through the `flowers` list, we update the `first_occurrence` and `last_occurrence` dictionaries. We also calculate the `prefix_sum` list, which only includes positive beauty values.\n\n3. **Maximum Beauty Calculation**: We iterate through the unique beauty values stored in `first_occurrence`. For each beauty value, we check if the first and last occurrences are different (i.e., there is more than one flower with this beauty value). If so, we calculate the total beauty of the valid garden that includes these two flowers and all flowers between them. We update `max_beauty` if this total beauty is greater than the current `max_beauty`.\n\n4. **Return Result**: Finally, we return the maximum beauty of any valid garden found.", "estimated_date": 1615075200000}